<Link id="l00150" /><CodeLine lineNumber="150"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Value that a single bit can take.  This is outside of the context of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00151" /><CodeLine lineNumber="151"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// any register, it is more of an abstraction of the two-element set of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00152" /><CodeLine lineNumber="152"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// possible bit values.  One extension here is the &quot;Ref&quot; type, which</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00153" /><CodeLine lineNumber="153"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// indicates that this bit takes the same value as the bit described by</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00154" /><CodeLine lineNumber="154"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// RefInfo.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00155" /><CodeLine lineNumber="155" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitvalue"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">struct </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitvalue">BitTracker::BitValue</a> &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00156" /><CodeLine lineNumber="156" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitvalue/#a8e191c51f58f07f7efa53510f3bdda94"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">enum</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitvalue/#a8e191c51f58f07f7efa53510f3bdda94">ValueType</a> &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00157" /><CodeLine lineNumber="157" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitvalue/#a8e191c51f58f07f7efa53510f3bdda94ac09b1529fd94175201a6edddd3a27c37"><span class="doxyHighlight">    <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitvalue/#a8e191c51f58f07f7efa53510f3bdda94ac09b1529fd94175201a6edddd3a27c37">Top</a>,    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Bit not yet defined.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00158" /><CodeLine lineNumber="158" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitvalue/#a8e191c51f58f07f7efa53510f3bdda94abab00433c23a81e220b50a1550320b9a"><span class="doxyHighlight">    <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitvalue/#a8e191c51f58f07f7efa53510f3bdda94abab00433c23a81e220b50a1550320b9a">Zero</a>,   </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Bit = 0</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00159" /><CodeLine lineNumber="159" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitvalue/#a8e191c51f58f07f7efa53510f3bdda94a86e84878fc26bf4a4fd39f94424b730b"><span class="doxyHighlight">    <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitvalue/#a8e191c51f58f07f7efa53510f3bdda94a86e84878fc26bf4a4fd39f94424b730b">One</a>,    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Bit = 1</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00160" /><CodeLine lineNumber="160" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitvalue/#a8e191c51f58f07f7efa53510f3bdda94a92811673861e6cd90e002880ed0ea153"><span class="doxyHighlight">    <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitvalue/#a8e191c51f58f07f7efa53510f3bdda94a92811673861e6cd90e002880ed0ea153">Ref</a>     </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Bit value same as the one described in RefI.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00161" /><CodeLine lineNumber="161"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Conceptually, there is no explicit &quot;bottom&quot; value: the lattice&#39;s</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00162" /><CodeLine lineNumber="162"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// bottom will be expressed as a &quot;ref to itself&quot;, which, in the context</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00163" /><CodeLine lineNumber="163"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// of registers, could be read as &quot;this value of this bit is defined by</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00164" /><CodeLine lineNumber="164"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// this bit&quot;.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00165" /><CodeLine lineNumber="165"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The ordering is:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00166" /><CodeLine lineNumber="166"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   x &lt;= Top,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00167" /><CodeLine lineNumber="167"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   Self &lt;= x, where &quot;Self&quot; is &quot;ref to itself&quot;.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00168" /><CodeLine lineNumber="168"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This makes the value lattice different for each virtual register</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00169" /><CodeLine lineNumber="169"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// (even for each bit in the same virtual register), since the &quot;bottom&quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00170" /><CodeLine lineNumber="170"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// for one register will be a simple &quot;ref&quot; for another register.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00171" /><CodeLine lineNumber="171"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Since we do not store the &quot;Self&quot; bit and register number, the meet</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00172" /><CodeLine lineNumber="172"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// operation will need to take it as a parameter.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00173" /><CodeLine lineNumber="173"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00174" /><CodeLine lineNumber="174"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// In practice there is a special case for values that are not associa-</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00175" /><CodeLine lineNumber="175"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// ted with any specific virtual register. An example would be a value</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00176" /><CodeLine lineNumber="176"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// corresponding to a bit of a physical register, or an intermediate</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00177" /><CodeLine lineNumber="177"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// value obtained in some computation (such as instruction evaluation).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00178" /><CodeLine lineNumber="178"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Such cases are identical to the usual Ref type, but the register</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00179" /><CodeLine lineNumber="179"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// number is 0 In such case the Pos field of the reference is ignored.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00180" /><CodeLine lineNumber="180"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00181" /><CodeLine lineNumber="181"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// What is worthy of notice is that in value V (that is a &quot;ref&quot;), as long</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00182" /><CodeLine lineNumber="182"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// as the RefI.Reg is not 0, it may actually be the same register as the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00183" /><CodeLine lineNumber="183"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// one in which V will be contained.  If the RefI.Pos refers to the posi-</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00184" /><CodeLine lineNumber="184"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// tion of V, then V is assumed to be &quot;bottom&quot; (as a &quot;ref to itself&quot;),</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00185" /><CodeLine lineNumber="185"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// otherwise V is taken to be identical to the referenced bit of the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00186" /><CodeLine lineNumber="186"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// same register.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00187" /><CodeLine lineNumber="187"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If RefI.Reg is 0, however, such a reference to the same register is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00188" /><CodeLine lineNumber="188"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// not possible.  Any value V that is a &quot;ref&quot;, and whose RefI.Reg is 0</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00189" /><CodeLine lineNumber="189"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// is treated as &quot;bottom&quot;.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00214" /><CodeLine lineNumber="214"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00215" /><CodeLine lineNumber="215"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The &quot;meet&quot; operation is the &quot;.&quot; operation in a semilattice (L, ., T, B):</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00216" /><CodeLine lineNumber="216"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// (1)  x.x = x</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00217" /><CodeLine lineNumber="217"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// (2)  x.y = y.x</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00218" /><CodeLine lineNumber="218"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// (3)  x.(y.z) = (x.y).z</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00219" /><CodeLine lineNumber="219"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// (4)  x.T = x  (i.e. T = &quot;top&quot;)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00220" /><CodeLine lineNumber="220"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// (5)  x.B = B  (i.e. B = &quot;bottom&quot;)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00221" /><CodeLine lineNumber="221"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00222" /><CodeLine lineNumber="222"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This &quot;meet&quot; function will update the value of the &quot;&#42;this&quot; object with</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00223" /><CodeLine lineNumber="223"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the newly calculated one, and return &quot;true&quot; if the value of &#42;this has</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00224" /><CodeLine lineNumber="224"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// changed, and &quot;false&quot; otherwise.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00225" /><CodeLine lineNumber="225"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// To prove that it satisfies the conditions (1)-(5), it is sufficient</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00226" /><CodeLine lineNumber="226"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// to show that a relation</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00227" /><CodeLine lineNumber="227"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   x &lt;= y  &lt;=&gt;  x.y = x</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00228" /><CodeLine lineNumber="228"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// defines a partial order (i.e. that &quot;meet&quot; is same as &quot;infimum&quot;).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00229" /><CodeLine lineNumber="229" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitvalue/#afce9aa6fea3ff538f2a94c8c56a34e04"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitvalue/#afce9aa6fea3ff538f2a94c8c56a34e04">meet</a>(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitvalue/#aee974ecd21a533055fdd11ec27e4febc">BitValue</a> &amp;V, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitref">BitRef</a> &amp;Self) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00230" /><CodeLine lineNumber="230"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// First, check the cases where there is nothing to be done.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00231" /><CodeLine lineNumber="231"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitvalue/#a093eda80cf560688e6c3578e8b7fd674">Type</a> == <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitvalue/#a8e191c51f58f07f7efa53510f3bdda94a92811673861e6cd90e002880ed0ea153">Ref</a> &amp;&amp; <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitvalue/#a6430b3f9e35d7d7e83399a565cfd143e">RefI</a> == Self)    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Bottom.meet(V) = Bottom (i.e. This)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00232" /><CodeLine lineNumber="232"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">false</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00233" /><CodeLine lineNumber="233"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (V.Type == <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitvalue/#a8e191c51f58f07f7efa53510f3bdda94ac09b1529fd94175201a6edddd3a27c37">Top</a>)                  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This.meet(Top) = This</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00234" /><CodeLine lineNumber="234"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">false</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00235" /><CodeLine lineNumber="235"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (&#42;</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">this</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> == V)                     </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This.meet(This) = This</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00236" /><CodeLine lineNumber="236"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">false</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00237" /><CodeLine lineNumber="237"></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00247" /><CodeLine lineNumber="247"><span class="doxyHighlight">    <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitvalue/#a093eda80cf560688e6c3578e8b7fd674">Type</a> = <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitvalue/#a8e191c51f58f07f7efa53510f3bdda94a92811673861e6cd90e002880ed0ea153">Ref</a>;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00248" /><CodeLine lineNumber="248"><span class="doxyHighlight">    <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/bittracker/bitvalue/#a6430b3f9e35d7d7e83399a565cfd143e">RefI</a> = Self;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00249" /><CodeLine lineNumber="249"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">true</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
